explanation: The loop only checked multiples of 5 from 0 to 95 (range(20)), so if N was near 100 the closest multiple (100) was never considered. I fixed the range to include 100 by iterating to 21. Only that single line was changed.
fixed_code:
N=int(input())
list=[]
for i in range(21):
  list.append(abs(N-i*5))
In=list.index(min(list))
print(In*5)
